Ask HN: What framework/language to use for this project?
text:
Hello HN!

Since 2016 I have been archiving episodes of a specific daily radio show in my country, which has a very niche but dedicated following of people. Since some fans can't listen to the show when it's live (work hours), a few people have been relying on me sharing the archives. I'm hosting all the episodes on multiple free plans of Mega.nz to have them available to share and I have a Wordpress blog setup to autopost links to new episodes from my VPS with a very basic bash program.

This setup is very stable (it has been on autopilot for the last couple years except minor fixes) but now I would like to remake it with more features. Since Whisper was released I've been very interested in trying to feed the whole archive (2000+ 2hrs episodes) into it and get a searchable transcript, so people could just search a name or a phrase and find out all the episodes where it was mentioned.

I recently watched the full CS50 course on YT and at the moment I'm undecided about which language to choose to create what I have in mind. So far I only studied c# in school, and python/html/css on my own. The website would have to list the episodes in some way from an SQL db, have it searchable by date (every episode name is the date it was aired), and ideally also have a search field for "text" that appears the transcript, which is still a work in progress.

What framework/language would you recommend? Is there a similar project you've done where I could take inspiration?

If you want you can contact me via the email in my profile, thanks!

Ask HN: How to deal with terrible R&D code?
text:
I'm working as a Backend Engineer at a product company. As part of my job, I integrate R&D code into the product. Most of the time, this R&D code is very terrible, badly-written, error-prone,... The frustration is growing day-by-day, release-by-release, as the R&D process still remains very horrible. Recently, I have to clean up a repository written entirely by a short-term intern, without any review from anyone else. She left the team recently, so no one grasps low-level details.

When I raise this issue with the engineering manager, he said that we have to accept this as a fact, as the R&D team does not care about code quality. Their work is to get things done, then leave them to the engineer team to figure out. The problem has been raised many times, but no solutions so far.

More context about the teams: The R&D team is located in California, while the engineering team (including me) is located in Hanoi. So communication is not very easy.

So my question is: How can I deal with this terrible process, or at least cope with the frustration.

Ask HN: What do you think about decentralized websites/apps?
text:
With Blockchain & IPFS tech maturing, it's becoming possible to create of fully decentralized websites.

What use-cases do you think would be uniquely suited to benefit from this? Are there any? Would you build one?

Or is existing Web2 infrastructure decentralized enough that there's little benefit to full decentralization?

E.g. Censorship-proof, ownership.

Ask HN: If money was no object what software would you create?
text:
Imagine you had a Sufficiently Large Budget to create the software you've always imagined. There are still hard problems, you can't just wish a revolutionary new operating system into existence of solve NP hard problems, but you don't have to worry about the budget.

What do you create?

(As a bonus question, what software would benefit humanity as a whole the most if it suddenly sprang into existence)
